    base:desc "Bidirectional communication between the Digital Twin and physical assets is facilitated through the same event stream used for telemetry. Control commands—such as HVAC setpoint adjustments, lighting level changes, and equipment operation changes—are embedded in the twin’s service layer and translated into actuator instructions sent to the physical devices. Validation and authorization of these commands are performed by the middleware, and execution confirmation is returned as acknowledgment events, forming a closed‑loop feedback system that resolves conflicts and ensures command consistency."
